               <scopecontent id="aspace_66fc5dfa1ab82c29f6967b505029ecb1">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Panels are approximately 30" high x 15" wide. They were a gift in 2004 of a delegation from the city of Zhuhai, China, and were produced for an exhibit there on Yung Wing. Each panel contains several images plus explanatory captions in both Chinese and English.</p>
                  <p>Yale Professor Emeritus of History Beatrice Bartlett examined the panels in 2005 and selected the following thirteen panels that she thought could make a stand-alone exhibit someplace at Yale: 3, 6-7, 9, 11, 13, 15-16, 19, 22, 24-25, and 27.</p>
